Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodianpottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '1.8'. Name Damokles. An example from the Athenian Agora, SS12374, is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (126)
